      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 3,
      "playtime_at_review": 188,
      "review_text": "I got hooked on the game from the demo it had and wanted to see what the full game would offer. I was not dissapointed, while it is, in a way, a quite simple game that is easy to get into. But don't let that fool you, just because it's simple in design doesn't mean it's not fun, quite the opposite, it's very fun because the ways you can play varies from both RNG and the modifiers you chose to play with and what you want to experiment with.\n\nThough there is room for improvemen, mostly in preformance at the later stages when you face off enemies that multiply into weaker ones and can tank the performance. That's honeslt the only negative thing I can say about the game.",
      "timestamp_created": 1773690675
    },
    {
      "review_id": "220901943",
      "author_steamid": "76561198046207397",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 0,
      "playtime_at_review": 311,
      "review_text": "This was a great find, blending tower defense with some rogue-like elements and factory organization it feels easy to pick up but not too simple. Runs great on SteamDeck until the later stages where there's just a ton of entities moving around. There's a few small nitpicks I have but the only one I would really say is necessary is the option to continue a run if I close out the game. I've abandoned a few runs already because of the lack of this feature and it would really help make it a great addition to your steamdeck library or even work laptop library if it was easier to put down at times.\n\n- other nitpick: can the directional arrows just be called their direction instead of having a specific name for each one? I'm constantly looking at the key guide to remember which one is which.",
      "timestamp_created": 1773760829
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221199182",
      "author_steamid": "76561198168879459",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 0,
      "playtime_at_review": 435,
      "review_text": "I enjoy it way more than i expected and than i'd like to admit.\r\nThat said, i wish there was a way to speed up the game even more.\r\nThere's also an issue of game turning into slideshow after about five waves of endless. Could benefit from some optimization",
      "timestamp_created": 1774040767
    }
  ]
